docs.abstract: Sixteen companies are calling for more transparency from the likes of Google and Facebook, and setting their own example in hopes of a less expensive, more efficient system.
docs.snippet: Sixteen companies are calling for more transparency from the likes of Google and Facebook, and setting their own example in hopes of a less expensive, more efficient system.
docs.lead_paragraph: A group of 16 companies — including leading ad tech firms, ad agencies and publishers — is trying to help clean up the murky world of digital advertising.

headline.main: The Online Ad World Is Murky. A Group of Companies Wants to Fix That.
headline.print_headline: Murkiness of Online Ads Spurs a Quest for Clarity

docs.abstract: Outracing the pack is overrated. But defining enough and then stopping there? It may be the best life shift you’ve made in ages.
docs.snippet: Outracing the pack is overrated. But defining enough and then stopping there? It may be the best life shift you’ve made in ages.
docs.lead_paragraph: Getting ahead is overrated as a goal. In fact, it might even be just plain stupid.

headline.main: How to Do Better Than Merely Getting Ahead

docs.abstract: The magazine was transferred to a new steward, Maven, and people familiar with the move said layoffs followed.
docs.snippet: The magazine was transferred to a new steward, Maven, and people familiar with the move said layoffs followed.
docs.lead_paragraph: Sports Illustrated, which set a standard for sportswriting and photography during its 20th-century heyday, was transferred to a new company Thursday. Along with the change, there were layoffs, according to three people with knowledge of the moves.

headline.main: Sports Illustrated Layoffs Seen as a Digital Company Takes Over
headline.print_headline: Layoffs Follow Transfer of Sports Illustrated’s Control

docs.abstract: New episodes will appear on the streaming platform nine months before they are shown on PBS. More than 4,500 shows from the “Sesame Street” library will also be available.
docs.snippet: New episodes will appear on the streaming platform nine months before they are shown on PBS. More than 4,500 shows from the “Sesame Street” library will also be available.
docs.lead_paragraph: “Sesame Street” is moving to a new streaming home.

headline.main: ‘Sesame Street,’ With Its Five-Decade Library, Moves to HBO Max

docs.abstract: The decision that individual countries can order Facebook to take down posts globally sets a benchmark for the reach of European laws governing the internet.
docs.snippet: The decision that individual countries can order Facebook to take down posts globally sets a benchmark for the reach of European laws governing the internet.
docs.lead_paragraph: LONDON — Europe’s top court said on Thursday that individual countries can order Facebook to take down posts, photographs and videos not only in their own countries but elsewhere, in a ruling that extends the reach of the region’s internet-related laws beyond its own borders.

headline.main: Facebook Can Be Forced to Delete Content Worldwide, E.U.’s Top Court Rules
headline.print_headline: E.U. Ruling On Facebook Crosses Borders

docs.abstract: The chief executive of International Workplace Group contends his company’s approach may not be as flashy but is more sustainable.
docs.snippet: The chief executive of International Workplace Group contends his company’s approach may not be as flashy but is more sustainable.
docs.lead_paragraph: In a few dizzying days last month, WeWork replaced its chief executive, withdrew its initial public offering and said it was slowing its breakneck expansion.

headline.main: As WeWork Slows Down, Biggest Competitor Says It’s Thriving
headline.print_headline: WeWork’s Woes Not Shared by Rival

docs.abstract: AdvoCare will pay $150 million to settle charges that it duped customers into thinking they could earn “unlimited income” distributing its products.
docs.snippet: AdvoCare will pay $150 million to settle charges that it duped customers into thinking they could earn “unlimited income” distributing its products.
docs.lead_paragraph: The N.F.L. star quarterback Drew Brees called it a “rewarding” opportunity, a chance to market health products trusted by thousands of people. Former President George W. Bush spoke at a sales conference in Texas designed to tout its “economic value.”

headline.main: Health Company Touted by Sports Stars Ran Pyramid Scheme, F.T.C. Says
headline.print_headline: F.T.C. Cites Pyramid Scheme in Fining Health Company

docs.abstract: The first major place in China to rebel against Beijing’s technologies of control is one of the last not yet fully under their thrall.
docs.snippet: The first major place in China to rebel against Beijing’s technologies of control is one of the last not yet fully under their thrall.
docs.lead_paragraph: HONG KONG — There’s no sign to mark it. But when travelers from Hong Kong cross into Shenzhen in mainland China, they reach a digital cutoff point.

headline.main: Hong Kong Takes Symbolic Stand Against China’s High-Tech Controls
headline.print_headline: Hong Kongers Poke Beijing In Digital Eyes
